caption.text: We've been sailing on the same sea and facing the waves together for nearly 3 years, on a boat we called SMAK IPEKA Pluit. The water was not always clean, the waves were not always exciting, and the sky was not always bright. But one thing, we WILL pass the biggest wave of all, the National Exam. Then, we may arrive on our destination, the full-of-satisfaction and gratitude-graduation day. But our boat wouldn't stop sailing. We will be back on the sea, each with our own boat, facing the real waves, going to the real destination called FUTURE, on a boat called UNIVERSITY. But WE, SIXERS, will always be under the same sky, and be brighten up by the same sun for the next 30 years, even more. We are just writing a new interesting story to be told when our boat meet again some other time in the next season. Maiden Voyage, Angkatan 6 SMAK IPEKA Pluit. Love, DSM.
